  "extraHighlightWords": [],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Wednesday. Once a month, Mr. Pan runs a current events class where we discuss real news from around the world instead of our textbook.",
      "zh": "星期三。潘老師每個月會上一次時事課，讓我們討論真實世界發生的新聞，而不是課本內容。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Today's topic covered international organizations that try to keep peace between countries when conflicts threaten to grow out of control.",
      "zh": "今天的主題是探討國際組織如何試圖在國家之間的衝突失控之前，維持彼此的和平。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"These organizations do not always succeed,\" Mr. Pan admitted honestly, \"but their existence still matters, especially during a serious crisis.\"",
      "zh": "「這些組織不一定每次都成功，」潘老師誠實地承認：「但它們的存在仍然很重要，尤其是在嚴重危機期間。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "He mentioned an old, historical example of a small region whose independence changed the political map of an entire continent.",
      "zh": "他提到一個古老的歷史例子：一個小地區的獨立，改變了整個大陸的政治版圖。"
    },
    {
      "en": "One student asked about terrorism, and Mr. Pan explained carefully that a terrorist attack tries to create fear rather than achieve any fair goal.",
      "zh": "有個同學問到恐怖主義，潘老師仔細解釋，恐怖攻擊的目的是製造恐懼，而不是達成任何公平的目標。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Fear spreads faster than facts,\" he said. \"Part of growing up is learning to slow down and examine information before reacting to it.\"",
      "zh": "他說：「恐懼傳播的速度比事實還快，」「長大的一部分，就是學會在做出反應之前，先冷靜下來檢視資訊。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "We also discussed a country's industry changing gradually over several decades, moving from farming toward modern technology and international trade.",
      "zh": "我們也討論了一個國家的產業如何在數十年間逐漸轉變，從農業走向現代科技和國際貿易。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Gradual change is harder to notice than sudden change,\" Mr. Pan said, \"but it usually shapes a nation's future far more deeply.\"",
      "zh": "潘老師說：「漸進式的改變比突然的改變更難察覺，」「但它通常對一個國家的未來影響更深遠。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "He showed us a map marking the capital of several countries, quizzing us in a friendly way that felt more like a game than a test.",
      "zh": "他給我們看一張標出好幾個國家首都的地圖，用一種比較像遊戲而不是考試的友善方式來考我們。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William's class, meanwhile, is apparently learning about their own city's local government, which felt oddly connected to what we discussed today.",
      "zh": "同時，William 那個班級顯然正在學他們自己城市的地方政府運作，這跟我們今天討論的內容意外地有連結。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice pointed out that most military conflicts we studied in history class eventually ended, sometimes taking generations, but eventually.",
      "zh": "Bernice 指出，我們歷史課學過的大部分軍事衝突，最後都結束了，有時候要花上好幾代人的時間，但終究還是結束了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"That is not always comforting,\" Mr. Pan replied, \"but it is honest. Nothing stays broken forever, even when it feels that way.\"",
      "zh": "潘老師回應：「這不一定讓人感到安慰，」「但這是誠實的。就算感覺起來如此，事情也不會永遠破碎下去。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "By the end of class, my notebook was full of unfamiliar country names, historical dates, and one very complicated map I will need to study again later.",
      "zh": "下課的時候，我的筆記本上塞滿了陌生的國家名稱、歷史日期，還有一張非常複雜、之後還得再研究一次的地圖。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Lesson of the day: the world is much bigger and much more complicated than my own street, my own school, or even my own small family.",
      "zh": "今日心得：這個世界比我自己住的街道、我的學校，甚至比我自己這個小家庭都還要大得多、複雜得多。"
    }
  ],
